I am not sure about initializing the config with every request. The config has the default value, you should not override it. Instead, you can check if there is the property specified in the request and use that value, else use the default value.
if (request.getRequestProperties().containsKey(key)) {
        return (Boolean) request.getRequestProperties().get(key);
}
else {
    return KsqlRequestConfig. KSQL_REQUEST_INTERNAL_REQUEST_DEFAULT;
}
